<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3733619>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Axinella arctica (Vosmaer, 1885): A. small specimen attached to pebble, thick stalk visible; B. underside of collected fragments; C. specimen amongst Duva sp. soft corals; D. specimen from B in situ; E. skeleton; F. spicules, oxeas and styles. In situ photo credit: DFO/CSSF/ArcticNet." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3733619/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

